s: February 26, 2025 - On April 1, 2014, Jack Link's bought Unilever's meat snack division in an attempt to expand its consumer base into Europe. The purchase includes the BiFi brand, sold across Europe and Peperami, which retails in the UK, Ireland and Mexico; and the manufacturing unit in Ansbach, Germany. In addition to traditional beef jerky, the company also manufactures bacon jerky, made with salt-and-sugar cured pork meat. In 2019 Jack Links acquired the Golden Island brand from Tyson Foods...
